Sentencas: Co-doped samples of Ce0.95-x Ca0.05Sr (x) O1.95-x , where (x = 0.00, 0.01, 0.02, and 0.03), have been prepared by auto-combustion method and characterized to explore their use as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Crystal structure, microstructure, and ionic conductivity have been characterized by X-ray diffraction, scanning electron microscopy, and impedance spectroscopy, respectively.
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All the compositions have been found to be single phase.
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Results show that the samples co-doped with Ca and Sr exhibit higher ionic conductivity than the samples singly doped with Ca in the intermediate temperature range.
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Ce0.93Ca0.05Sr0.02O2-delta exhibits maximum conductivity among all the compositions.
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: This may be a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Ceria co-doped with calcium (Ca) and strontium (Sr): a potential candidate as a solid electrolyte for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
